description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a Specialist Speech and Language Therapist to join our &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;dynamic and friendly team based at Crawley Hospital. This is a permanent part time post of 22.5 hours per week, with additional hours (7.5, 0.2 WTE) being available until January 2022. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will see patients in the community across Crawley, Horsham and Mid Sussex in their own homes, nursing homes and outpatient clinics. They will work on a varied caseload of both progressive and non-progressive conditions, with adults presenting with a range of communication and swallowing difficulties. They will need experience of interdisciplinary team working, supporting junior colleagues and students, training delivery, and involvement in clinical governance activities. Post-qualification dysphagia training and experience is essential. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;SCFT provides a high quality, responsive and evidence-based Speech and Language Therapy service, and we actively encourage personal and professional development of clinical, analytical, research and leadership skills. This is an exciting time to join us, as we are planning new and innovative ways to deliver our services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Esther Larsson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Services Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;esther.larsson1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07557 499594&lt;/p&gt;
